      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:142:6",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) لَا تَقْطَعْ رَحِمَكَ وَ إِنْ قَطَعَتْكَ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Al Nowfaly, from Al Sakuny, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘Do not cut off your relatives and even if they cut you off’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "6. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from al-Nawfali from al-Sakuni from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “The Messenger of Allah has said, ‘Do not fail to maintain good relations with relatives, even if they fail to maintain good relations with you.’” "
        ]
      }
